      <description>&lt;p&gt;Jan 3rd or 4th&amp;hellip; what day even is it?&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Today have taken the opportunity, whilst recovering from a really nasty &amp;lsquo;flu bug, to fall down the rabbit hole of not one, but two fantastic public domain image sites. There&amp;rsquo;s the Public Domain Image Archive, which I think is based in the UK.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;    &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;link-preview&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;preview-text&#34;&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;strong&gt;Public Domain Image Archive&lt;/strong&gt;&#xA;    &lt;p&gt;Explore our hand-picked collection of 10,046 out-of-copyright works, free for all to browse, download, and reuse.&#xA;                                This is a living database with new images added every week.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
